// Slice-set (lvalue): assign into a bit range of a `var`. Two tiling slice-sets
// build a 16-bit word from two bytes (planning/slicing.md). Each `word[hi..lo]`
// lowers to a part-select on the LHS: `word[7:0] = lo_byte`, `word[15:8] = hi_byte`.
fn concat(lo_byte: bits(8), hi_byte: bits(8)) -> bits(16) {
    var word: bits(16);
    word[8..0] = lo_byte;
    word[16..8] = hi_byte;
    return word;
}
